\n< Serena >I've already drained this girl. Let's find another
cow.
\n< Serena >Like this, like this, like this.
\n< Serena >Like this, like this, like this.

\n< Serena >Hmm... I have only seen things like milk in a
container, so I had only recognized them as being
like that from the beginning...

\n< Serena >I feel strange. I might not be able to drink milk
anymore with the same flat feeling as before.

\n< Farmer >Is that how it is? For us, on the contrary, we
don't feel anything anymore.

\n< Farmer >Well, originally it's meant for the mother cow to
feed her calf.

\n< Farmer >It's a strange story when you think about it, that
we humans are squeezing it and drinking it.

\n< Farmer >I wonder who was the first person to think of
drinking it...
\n< Serena >Mother, to the child...
\n< Serena >Hm? So, does this cow have a child?

\n< Farmer >Well, that's right. Dairy cows are pregnant all
year round.
\n< Serena >Pregnancy...?? What does that have to do with milk?

\n< Farmer >Haa, what a strange girl. She must be quite
sheltered.

\n< Farmer >You see, mother cows produce milk from their
udders to feed their calves.

\n< Farmer >In other words, they start producing milk only
after they have a child.

\n< Farmer >Clever humans take advantage of the nature of
these animals and have the cows get pregnant all
year round to produce milk for us.
\n< Serena >Hm...

\n< Farmer >Is it really that strange? Basically, all animals,
not just cows, produce milk, you know.

\n< Farmer >You were sucking on your mother's milk until just
the other day, weren't you?
\n< Serena >E-even humans too!?

\n< Farmer >That's impossible. Where can you find a human who
grew up without sucking on their mother's milk?
\n< Serena >I...

\n< Serena >...No, come to think of it... I vaguely remember
clinging to my wet nurse's chest...

\n< Serena >So, if a child is born, will you also be able to
produce milk?
\n< Farmer >Me? Ahahaha!!
\n< Serena >Hm...?

\n< Farmer >I don't produce milk. It's the mother's job to
produce milk, after all.

\n< Farmer >Actually, it's more like your job, not mine, to
produce milk.
\n< Serena >M-me!?
\n< Serena >L-Like this...?

\n< Farmer >The size of human and cow milk is different, you
know. It shouldn't be possible with that kind of
force.
\n< Serena >I-I see...

\n< Farmer >Well, I guess it's just preparation for someday.
I'll give it a squeeze.

\n< Serena >It's even more difficult for me to do it when you
say things like that...
\n< Serena >.......

\n< Farmer >Do we even need any more cheers? You've gotten
completely used to it, haven't you?
セレナ HK_FM01-1
セレナ HK_FM01-1

\n< Serena >Even though you say I've gotten used to it, I'm
only working at half the speed of the master.

\n< Farmer >Well, I mean, we're making a living off of this,
after all.

\n< Farmer >Well, I'm done now. Can I leave the other two to
you?

\n< Serena >Understood.

\n< Farmer >Well then, I'll start cleaning up. Hehe, I

\n< Farmer >Hmmm...
\n< Serena >....
\n< Serena >....
\n< Farmer >Hmmm...

\n< Serena >Ah, Master. What's the matter ? It's just that I
can't help but feel conscious when you're staring
at me from behind.

\n< Farmer >Well, looking at it this way, you don't have the height, but I must say
you've got a nice ass.
\n< Serena >?? What do you mean by that...?

\n< Farmer >It's nothing, it's nothing. Just keep going
without worrying about it.
\n< Serena >U-um....
\n< Farmer >Hmmm... quite... mmm!
\n< Serena >Ugh, I'm curious...

\n< Serena >Hmm, it seems she won't come out anymore. You've
been very well-behaved, good job.

\n< Serena >Master, it's finished, but... why are you lying
on the ground?
\n< Farmer >No, I thought maybe if I did this...
\n< Serena >I wonder what it is?
\n< Farmer >I wonder what it is...

\n< Serena >??... Anyway, the work is done. Can we consider
the request completed with this?
\n< Farmer >Huh? Oh... Ah! That's right!
モブ HK_おっさん01-4
モブ HK_おっさん01-4

\n< Farmer >Of course, of course. This is the last one. Phew,
I'm saved, I'm saved.
\n< Farmer >I'll make sure to inform the guild about it, okay?

\n< Farmer >...If possible, I would like you, a skilled
adventurer like yourself, to come and help again.

\n< Serena >I'm sorry, but I'm also in a hurry, so I can't
make any guarantees.

\n< Serena >However, if we can come to an agreement, I would
like to visit again.

\n< Serena >There is a difference between horses and cows, but
it was fun to interact with animals after a long
time...

\n< Farmer >Hehe. Is that so, is that so? Well then, I'll be
counting on you again.
\n< Serena >Ah, well then.
\n< Guild Master >Oh, you're back. How did it go?

\n< Serena >It ended without any problems. Please make a
record of the completed request.

\n< Guild Master >No, it's not about that... If there are no
problems, then that's even better...

\n< Guild Master >Well, never mind. This is the reward for this
request.
\n< Serena >Hmm... \V[2501] more to go.

\n< Serena >It's a rope.

\n< Serena >There are countless ways to use it on a farm like
this, I suppose.
\n< Serena >It's a feeding box.
\n< Serena >I scoop it from here and feed it to the livestock.

\n< Serena >I've done it once before, but it's a very labor-
intensive job, so I had someone else take over for
me.
\n< Serena >Whip.

\n< Serena >They say that when livestock refuses to listen,
you can use this to threaten them by hitting the
ground.

\n< Serena >Judging by the amount of dust it's collecting, it
seems like this isn't used much around here.
\n< Serena >...So, what's with this outfit?

\n< Farmer >You can't work in the stable while wearing such a
beautiful dress, can you?
\n< Serena >Well, that's true but...
\n< Farmer >It's good that the child-sized one fits.

\n< Farmer >So... you're used to handling livestock, but you
don't have any experience with milking, is that
right?

\n< Serena >Hmm. But I'm confident in my ability to learn
quickly. If you show me a little, I think I can do
it right away.

\n< Farmer >Oh, I see. Well then, I'll show you how to milk
right now. Pay close attention and learn well.

\n< Farmer >Hold it like this, and bring your fingers like
this, and like this.

\n< Farmer >There it is. Keep doing it until it stops coming
out.
\n< Serena >Th-This is coming out so forcefully...?
\n< Farmer >Haha, surprising, isn't it?

\n< Serena >I was expecting it to come out a little more
smoothly...

\n< Farmer >Well, these little ones are stuffing milk into
this huge udder, you know.

\n< Farmer >Well, it's natural for it to come out forcefully.
It's different from a mother's breasts, you know?
\n< Serena >...？

\n< Serena >I roughly understand. Since I'll show you, is it

\n< Serena >Having a good memory is one of the few things I'm

\n< Serena >Well, if there are no problems, I would like to
